While a minimum wage was obtained during the third Merkel cabinet in 2015 after large union pressure and nationwide protests, the capitalists, through the <span style="color: #98C22C;">**NLP**</span> have heavily watered down the proposal - just enough to prevent further backlash, but not to a large enough scale as to truly reduce economic inequality. Ever since then, increasing the minimum wage to a liveable one has been an important part of our campaigning.

